!!! 5
%html
  %head
    %title jQAPI - Alternative jQuery Documentation Browser

    %meta{:name => "content-type", :content => "text/html; charset=utf-8"}
    %meta{:name => "description", :content => "Alternative jQuery Documentation Browser"}
    
    %link{:href  => '/assets/bundle.css', :type => 'text/css', :rel => 'stylesheet'}
    %script{:src => '/assets/bundle.js',  :type => 'text/javascript'}
  
  %body
    #sidebar
      #search
        %input#search-field{:type => 'search', :placeholder => 'Search', :autocomplete => 'off', :autosave => 'searchdoc',  :results => '0', :autofocus => 'autofocus'}

      #sidebar-content
        %ul#categories
          %li.loader Loading...

        %ul#results.entries
          %li.not-found Nothing found.

    #content
      #header
        %ul#signatures-nav
          %li
            %a{:href => '#about'}
              %span What is this about?
          %li
            %a{:href => '#usage'}
              %span Usage
          %li
            %a{:href => '#download'}
              %span Download
          %li
            %a{:href => '#credits'}
              %span Credits
          %li
            %a{:href => '#license'}
              %span License
          %li
            %a{:href => '#changelog'}
              %span Changelog
        
        %ul#navigation
          %li
            %a{:href => '/'}
              %span Home

      #entry
        #entry-wrapper
          #entry-header
            %h1 jQAPI - Alternative jQuery Documentation Browser
            %p The faster way to browse the jQuery documentation.

          %ul#entries
            %li.entry
              %ul.signatures
                %li.signature
                  %h2.title What is this about?

                  .row.clearfix
                    .left#intro
                      %p
                        This is a alternative interface to browse the
                        %a{:href => 'http://api.jquery.com'} Official jQuery Documentation
                        that can be found on
                        %a{:href => 'https://github.com/jquery/api.jquery.com'} GitHub
                        \.

                      %p
                        The aim of this project is to get out of the way of your development work. 
                        Quickly switch to this docs and find what you are looking for.

                      %p
                        Furthermore you can download this documentation and browse it offline.
                        In the future you don't even need to download it to have it available
                        offline.

                      %p
                        This
                        %a{:href => 'https://github.com/jqapi/jqapi'} Open-Source
                        project is still in development. If you are having trouble with it
                        you can still visit the
                        %a{:href => 'http://old.jqapi.com'} old jQAPI
                        \.

